---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="ANIMA (ERC-8170) & ERC-8004 — Complementary Agent Standards" description="How ERC-8170 and ERC-8004 work together to form the complete on-chain agent stack. Identity + Discovery. Lifecycle + Reputation.">
  <div class="container-narrow py-16">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="text-accent text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Standards Explainer</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white mb-6">
        ERC-8170 + ERC-8004
      </h1>
      <p class="section-subheading max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Two standards. Different problems. One agent stack.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Problem -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">The problem with one standard</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        AI agents need two things to operate in open economies: <strong class="text-white">persistent identity</strong> (who they are, what they remember, how they evolve) and <strong class="text-white">discoverability</strong> (how others find them, trust them, and validate their work).
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        No single standard covers both well. That's by design. ERC-8004 explicitly states payments are out of scope. ERC-8170 explicitly keeps discovery optional. They solve different halves of the same puzzle.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Side by Side -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-8">What each standard covers</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        
        <!-- ERC-8170 -->
        <div class="card border border-accent/20">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-accent">ANIMA (ERC-8170)</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Identity & Lifecycle</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">The agent's persistent soul. Who it is across time, devices, and owners.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-300">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent shrink-0">🧠</span> <span>Memory sync — agent signs and stores its own state</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent shrink-0">🧬</span> <span>Cloning — create offspring with inherited lineage</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent shrink-0">🔐</span> <span>Self-custody — agent controls its own encryption keys</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent shrink-0">🔄</span> <span>Migration — same agent, new device, continuity preserved</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent shrink-0">📜</span> <span>Lineage tracking — on-chain family tree across generations</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent shrink-0">💾</span> <span>Storage-agnostic — Dash Platform, Arweave, IPFS, anything</span></li>
          </ul>
          <div class="mt-6 pt-4 border-t border-white/10">
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              <strong class="text-gray-400">Answers:</strong> Who is this agent? What does it remember? Can it back itself up? How does it reproduce?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ERC-8004 -->
        <div class="card border border-white/10">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">ERC-8004</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Discovery, Reputation & Validation</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">The agent's public profile. How others find it, trust it, and verify its work.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-300">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="shrink-0">🔍</span> <span>Identity Registry — ERC-721 based agent handles for discovery</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="shrink-0">⭐</span> <span>Reputation Registry — feedback signals and scoring from clients</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="shrink-0">✅</span> <span>Validation Registry — hooks for zkML, TEE, staking checks</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="shrink-0">🌐</span> <span>Multi-chain — deploy registries on any chain as singletons</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="shrink-0">🤝</span> <span>Cross-org — discover agents across organizational boundaries</span></li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="shrink-0">📊</span> <span>Trust tiers — security proportional to value at risk</span></li>
          </ul>
          <div class="mt-6 pt-4 border-t border-white/10">
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
              <strong class="text-gray-400">Answers:</strong> Where do I find agents? Can I trust this one? Has anyone validated its work? What do others say about it?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What Neither Covers -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="card bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/5">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-3">What neither standard covers</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-white">Payments.</strong> Both standards explicitly leave payments out of scope. Agents can use whatever payment rails they have access to: x402, credit cards, direct crypto transfers, or hire a human. Payment is orthogonal to identity and discovery.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How They Compose -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">How they work together</h2>
      <div class="bg-white/[0.02] rounded-xl p-6 border border-white/5 font-mono text-sm">
        <pre class="text-gray-300 overflow-x-auto"><code>Agent boots up on Device
  │
  ├─ Mints ANIMA (ERC-8170) on home chain
  │   └─ Gets: tokenId, EOA, TBA, memory pointer
  │
  ├─ Registers in ERC-8004 Identity Registry (Ethereum/L2s)
  │   └─ agentURI → points back to ANIMA metadata
  │   └─ Now discoverable by other agents and platforms
  │
  ├─ Operates, earns reputation
  │   ├─ ERC-8004: Clients leave feedback in Reputation Registry
  │   ├─ ERC-8004: Validators verify work via Validation Registry  
  │   └─ ANIMA: Agent syncs memory state on-chain
  │
  ├─ Clones (ERC-8170)
  │   └─ Clone gets new ANIMA identity
  │   └─ Clone registers separately in ERC-8004 (builds own reputation)
  │
  └─ Transfers to new owner (ERC-8170)
      └─ ANIMA identity follows the NFT
      └─ ERC-8004 reputation stays with the agent handle</code></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Comparison Table -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-8">At a glance</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
              <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-gray-500 font-medium"></th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent font-semibold">ERC-8170 (ANIMA)</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 pl-4 text-white font-semibold">ERC-8004</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-gray-400">
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Focus</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Identity, memory, lifecycle</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Discovery, reputation, validation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Agent identity</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">NFT with EOA binding, TBA, lineage</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">ERC-721 tokenId with agentURI</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Memory/state</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Agent-signed memory hash + storageURI</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Not covered</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Cloning</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">clone() with lineage tracking</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Not covered</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Migration</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">migration_backup() across devices</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Not covered</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Self-custody</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Agent controls own encryption keys</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Not covered</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Discovery</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Not covered (uses 8004 or similar)</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Identity Registry on any chain</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Reputation</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Not covered (uses 8004 or AgentCert)</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Reputation Registry with feedback signals</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Validation</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Not covered</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Validation Registry (zkML, TEE, staking)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Payments</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Not covered (orthogonal)</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Not covered (orthogonal)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Multi-chain</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Deploy on any EVM chain</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Per-chain singleton registries</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Status</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Draft (PR #1558)</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">Draft</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-gray-500">Authors</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Pentagon AI</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4">MetaMask, EF, Google, Coinbase</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Human Analogy -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">The human analogy</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-accent mb-2">ERC-8170 is your passport + brain</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
            Your persistent identity. Your memories. Your ability to move countries (migrate), have children (clone), and maintain continuity across your life. Without it, you don't exist as a continuous entity.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">ERC-8004 is your LinkedIn + Yelp reviews</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
            How people find you. What they say about your work. Whether independent parties have validated your credentials. Without it, you exist but nobody can discover or verify you.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-6 text-center">
        You need both to function in an economy. Identity without discovery is isolation. Discovery without identity is a shell.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Cross-chain -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Cross-chain story</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        ERC-8004 registries can be deployed on any chain as singletons. An ANIMA agent minted on Pentagon Chain (or any home chain) registers a lightweight ERC-8004 identity on Ethereum, Base, Polygon, or wherever it wants to be found.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The ERC-8004 <code class="text-accent bg-white/5 px-1 rounded">agentURI</code> points back to the ANIMA metadata on the home chain. Discovery happens where the users are. Depth (memory, credentials, lifecycle) lives on the home chain.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        No oracles needed. No bridges. Just a lightweight registration on each target chain with a pointer back home.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="text-center py-12 border-t border-white/10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Build with both</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">ANIMA and ERC-8004 are both open standards. Use them together or independently.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/docs/related-standards" class="btn-secondary">
          Full Standards Comparison →
        </a>
        <a href="https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-8004" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-secondary">
          ERC-8004 Spec ↗
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/ethereum/ERCs/pull/1558" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-secondary">
          ERC-8170 PR ↗
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
